// Control plane for mod_open_switch.
//
// Callers (orchestrators, bots, agents) invoke these RPCs to drive
// FreeSWITCH from outside. The module exposes this service in-process so
// no extra hop is required.
//
// Idempotency: write methods are idempotent when `request_id` is
// supplied. The module's per-process LRU cache (default TTL 300s)
// returns the cached response — success OR error — for duplicate
// `(tenant_id, request_id)` within the window. While the original
// is in flight, retries block on an in-flight marker with a shadow
// deadline = min(gRPC deadline, idempotency_in_flight_max_wait).
